OL,5, Tougher rules over which homes can be  
OL,6, forcibly switched to a prepayment      
OL,7, energy meter have been criticised by   
OL,8, campaigners who want a total ban.      
OL,10,FCustomers must be given more chance to 
OL,11,Fclear debts and forced meter fittings  
OL,12,Fwill be banned in homes with residents 
OL,13,Fall aged over 85, regulator Ofgem said.
OL,15,FCharities say the measures are not     
OL,16,Fenough because they are voluntary, but 
OL,17,FOfgem says they will soon be mandatory.
OL,19,FFitting was halted after agents broke  
OL,20,Finto the homes of vulnerable people.   
